This man is near catatonic with fear and despair. He heaves quiet, inconsolable sobs, wild eyes darting or wincing shut at every sudden noise. While there are signs of physical injury, it becomes obvious that the greater intent of his condition is to inflict psychological harm.

Although his gaze staggers across the passage of something other than his captors, he doesn't seem to register them as anything more than one more terrible component of his tormenting environment. Besides anxious flinching, he is unresponsive to any attempts at communication.
This outcropping seems sturdy enough that you could attach a rope to it to throw down the cliff side, making climbing far easier for any others traveling with you.

This rock face, though quite steep, has many crags and outcroppings that could be used to climb by a strong individual. Should you fall while climbing however only cold, unyielding stone awaits below...
Light from the moon or sun filters down through fissures in the ceiling. The cracks are too small to conceiveably climb through, but they do allow the passage of fresh air.
